e problems with each other, they are worked out in personal tells. If there are further issues, contact a council member to assist you. There will be no pissing matches in any channel outside of personal tells. There will be no exceptions to this. If you have an issue with something related to the guild as a whole, contact a council member. <br><br>Relations with other guilds on the server will be managed exclusively by the council member responsible for public relations. If you become aware of an issue with another guild let the public relations council member know and s/he will handle it. In situations where relations between Sacrosanct and another guild are strained, it is very important that this policy is followed. Again, the bottom line is we are a professional guild and issues are handled in a professional manner. As individual members of Sacrosanct, we do not flame other guilds or attack them publicly. If a situation requires a heated public discussion, it will be managed by the public relations council member.<br><br>Sacrosanct is a raiding guild. Members are individually responsible to get to level 60 and this should be a priority for them. Playing an alternate character is not prohibited, however, we strongly encourage players to focus on reaching level 60 with their primary character before playing alternates. While it is acceptable to ask for ports, rezes and groups in guild chat outside of a raid situation, and we encourage members to offer these services, it is not the guild's responsibility to provide them. Whining and spamming the guild channel regarding these issues will not be tolerated.<br><br>In order to prevent a revolving door policy and the use of de-guilding oneself to express disapproval of some issue, members that remove themselves from the guild will not be allowed to return unless a unanimous exception is made by the guild council and at least two weeks has passed. We take deguilding oneself very seriously. In cases of guild tag bugs, please contact a council member for re-tagging.<br><br>Discipline issues will be handled collectively by the council. The process is as follows. If a guild member is acting in a way that requires discipline, the council will discuss the issue and vote on whether or not to give the member an official warning. If the voting is unanymous, the member will be officially warned. The official warning is just that, a warning. The member will be contacted and informed that s/he is being officially warned regarding his or her conduct. If the problem continues another vote will be taken to suspend the member for one week. If the vote is unanymous, the member will be deguilded for a week and will not be permitted to attend guild functions. After a week, the member will be reguilded. If the problem continues to persist, a third vote will be taken to perminently deguild the member. If the vote is unanymous, the player will be informed of this and removed from the guild. The bottom line here is be professional. If you are acting in an unacceptable fashion, you will be informed of that and eventually removed from the guild if you do not change for the better.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub46.ezboard.com/uslaas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slaas</A> at: 8/22/01 11:31:26 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showNextMessage?topicID=2.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.sacrosanctguild.com/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><im